  %% HostSession now connects to the agent's configured host bind address (spawn_worker -> connect_channel::<SessionMessage>), owns a single per-connection Executor built by Executor::new(agent_tx), and pumps inbound SessionMessage envelopes through run_worker -> unwrap message.event -> Executor::route_session_event over a current-thread tokio runtime; new(name) stores the session name in SOURCE_NAME and HostSession exposes a static package_message(SessionEvent) -> SessionMessage; close signals the shutdown flag and joins the worker. The executor is a single route_session_event router (intercepts Evoke into create_execution to spawn+track an ExecutionRuntime, and forwards other execution events to the target ExecutionRuntime via executions.with), while the execution runtime and ToolRegistry are implemented. Executor::new(agent_tx) stores the shared agent SessionMessage sender and builds a ToolRegistry that reads the global Config and loads Tool handles from the configured tool directory.
  %% main.rs is the marix-host binary entry that loads the global Config and runs HostSession::new(config.name).
  subgraph main_rs[main.rs marix-host bin]
    MarixHostBin["marix-host\nbin entry: Config + HostSession"]
  end

  subgraph session_rs[session.rs]
